The '''Lincoln Library of Essential Information''' also called '''The New Lincoln Library Encyclopedia''' is an [[Encyclopedia|abridged encyclopedia]].<ref name="KentLancour1978">{{cite book|last1=Kent|first1=Allen|last2=Lancour|first2=Harold|last3=Daily|first3=Jay E.|title=Encyclopedia of Library and Information Science: Volume 25 - Publishers and the Library to Rochester: University of Rochester Library|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l8mIFaw53JUC&pg=PA172|accessdate=6 April 2011|date=1 June 1978|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-0-8247-2025-4|page=172}}</ref> The encyclopedia is "named after [[Abraham Lincoln]], whose inspiring example demonstrated the possibilities of self education."<ref>{{cite book|title=Lincoln Library of Essential Information|page=title page}}</ref>
