hop)|James Pilkington]] |''Works'' |1842 |[[James Scholefield]] |- |[[Nicholas Ridley (bishop)|Nicholas Ridley]] |''Works'' |1841 |Henry Christmas |- |[[Thomas Rogers (clergyman)|Thomas Rogers]] |''The Catholic Doctrine of the Church of England: An exposition of the Thirty-nine articles'' |1854 |[[John James Stewart Perowne]] |- |[[Edwin Sandys (bishop)|Edwin Sandys]] |''Sermons'' |1841 |John Ayre |- |[[William Tyndale]] |''Doctrinal Treatises, and Introductions to different portions of the Holy Scriptures'' |1848 |[[Henry Walter (antiquarian)|Henry Walter]] |- | |''Expositions and Notes on sundry portions of the Holy Scriptures'' |1849 |Henry Walter |- | |''An Answer to Sir Thomas More's Dialogue'' |1850 |Henry Walter |- |[[William Whitaker (theologian)|William Whitaker]] |''A Disputation on Holy Scripture against the Papists'' |1849 |[[William Fitzgerald (bishop)|William Fitzgerald]] |- |[[John Whitgift]] |''Works'' (three vols.) |1851–3 |John Ayre |- |[[John Woolton]] |''The Christian Manual'' |1851 | |}
