{{distinguish|text=Louise Bourgeois' similar sculpture, [[Maman (sculpture)]]}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = File:National gallery, sculptures gallery, spider.JPG | caption = <small>One edition at the [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]] in Washington, D.C.</small> | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 330px | title = Spider | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Louise Bourgeois | year = 1996 | type = Sculpture | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = 9 | height_inch = 3 | width_imperial = 27 | width_inch = 4 | length_imperial = 26 | metric_unit = m | imperial_unit = ft | city = | museum = | coordinates = | owner = }}
'''''Spider''''' is a sculpture by [[Louise Bourgeois]].<ref name="SIRIS">[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=FX01327960E26.20894&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!338951~!0&ri=20&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=spider+bourgeois&index=.GW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=20#focus "Spider, (sculpture)"]. ''[[SIRIS]]''</ref> Executed in 1996 as an edition of six and cast in 1997; bronze with a [[silver nitrate]] patina, with the first of the edition being steel.<ref name="Christie's"/>
An example was acquired by the [[Denver Art Museum]] for its new addition in 2006.<ref>{{cite news|last=MacMillan|first=Kyle|title=Not all the art is within the walls|url=http://www.denverpost.com/artmuseum/ci_4435717|accessdate=18 November 2012|newspaper=The Denver Post|date= 5 October 2006}}</ref> Other locations in permanent collections include the [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]], Washington DC,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nga.gov/feature/sculpturegarden/sculpture/sculpture3.shtm|title= NGA : Sculpture Garden (3 of 17)}}</ref> and the [[Kemper Museum of Contemporary Art]], [[Kansas City, Missouri]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Louise Bourgeois|url=https://www.kemperart.org/permanent/works/BourgeoisSpider.asp|work=Permanent Collection|publisher=Kemper Museum of Contemporary Ar|accessdate=22 January 2014}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The steel ''Spider'' was exhibited at [[Musée d'art contemporain de Montréal]] from April to September, 1996.<ref name="Christie's" /> Various editions of this artwork have traveled extensively, including an example shown at the [[Hermitage Museum]] in 2001.<ref name="Hermitage">{{cite web|url= http://www.hermitagemuseum.org/html_En/13/hm13_2_001.html|title= Louise Bourgeois's Spiders in the Hermitage|publisher= State Hermitage Museum|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110629131206/http://www.hermitagemuseum.org/html_En/13/hm13_2_001.html|archivedate= 2011-06-29|df= }}</ref>
==Art market== In 2006, Bourgeois became the highest-paid living woman artist after a ''Spider'' sold for $4 million at [[Christie's]] in London; which was surpassed in 2008, when another ''Spider'' sold for $4.5 million.<ref>Felix Kessler (May 31, 2010), [https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-05-31/louise-bourgeois-sculptor-of-freakish-spiders-erotic-limbs-dies-at-98.html Louise Bourgeois, Sculptor of Freaky Giant Spiders, Dies at 98] ''[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]''.</ref> A new record price for the artist was achieved when ''Spider'' number two acquired from [[Gallery Paule Anglim]], San Francisco, was auctioned by a private collector with an estimate of $4 million to $6 million. The price realized at Christie's on 8 November 2011 was $10,722,500.<ref name="Christie's">{{cite web|title=Louise Bourgeois (1911-2010) ''Spider''|url=http://www.christies.com/lotfinder/sculptures-statues-figures/louise-bourgeois-spider-5496701-details.aspx|publisher=Christie's Inc.|accessdate=25 January 2014|work=Sale 2480 / Lot 29}}</ref> This is the highest price paid for an artwork by a woman artist at the time.<ref>{{cite news|title=The price of being female: Post-war artists at auction|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/prospero/2012/05/post-war-artists-auction|work=Prospero blog|publisher=The Economist|accessdate=21 January 2014|date=25 May 2012}}</ref> This was surpassed in 2015 by a ''Spider'' auctioned by Christie's for $28.2 million.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Reyburn|first1=Scott|last2=Pogrebin|first2=Robin|title=Mixed Night in ‘Strange’ Christie’s Contemporary and Postwar Sale|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/11/arts/design/mixed-night-in-strange-christies-contemporary-and-postwar-sale.html?_r=0|work=The New York Times|date=10 November 2015}}</ref>
