'''''The Cambridge Edition of the Letters of Ernest Hemingway''''' is an ongoing scholarly multi-volume publication of the letters of [[Ernest Hemingway]] undertaken by the [[Cambridge University Press]]. Out of the projected 16 volumes, the first volume, covering years from 1907 to 1922, was published in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridge.org/us/knowledge/isbn/item6216997/The%20Letters%20of%20Ernest%20Hemingway/?site_locale=en_US |title=Letters Ernest Hemingway Volume 1 :: American literature :: Cambridge University Press |publisher=Cambridge.org |date=2011-07-05 |accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref> The project, when completed, will collect every extant Hemingway letter, numbering over 6,000, and is being edited by [[Sandra Spanier]], professor of English at [[Pennsylvania State University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeblog.org/2011/07/5-questions-with-sandra-spanier |title=An Interview with the General Editor of The Letters of Ernest Hemingway &#124; fifteeneightyfour |publisher=Cambridgeblog.org |date= |accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref> The second volume, covering years from 1923 to 1925, was scheduled to be published in the fall of 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hemingwaysociety.org/Default.aspx?content=letters.txt |accessdate=May 24, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723092000/http://hemingwaysociety.org/Default.aspx?content=letters.txt |archivedate=July 23, 2011 }}</ref> The project may take 20 years to finish.<ref>{{cite web|last=Howard |first=Jennifer |url=http://chronicle.com/article/Hemingways-Newly-Released/129337/ |title=Hemingway's Newly Released Letters Cast Author in New Light - Research - The Chronicle of Higher Education |publisher=Chronicle.com |date=2011-10-10 |accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref>

